        "created_at": "2025-03-14T02:51:51.279Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I connected with a group of people at a few events.  We kept up for a long while via Signal before it had usernames, but my number has changed, and I don’t have email nor physical addresses for the contacts.  I want to invite several contacts with my Signal username, but to cover my new phone number. (old number is gone)  Can Signal do that in initial link invites, or does it have to use SMS and expose the sender’s phone number initially?</p>",
