        "id": 263556,
        "name": "",
        "username": "roscoe",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/258eb7/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-03-14T07:13:25.904Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I backed up Signal contacts before deleting the account and unsubscribing the old number.  All I have is phone numbers for a number of friends (old Signal account/number and phone are gone).  As I said, I don’t have email addresses or other contact info for some people that I want to reconnect with (only phone numbers).  Can a Signal invite work as follows:</p>\n<p>“  Hi “Bob”, it’s “Alice” from our old group “meetings” at the “events” and our Signal chats.  Would you like to reconnect with me here.  My phone/number have changed, so please use my Signal username (myusername.##) to complete this Signal link-request.  We could voice-verify after connecting, and if several from the group want to reconnect, I’ll try to arrange a group meeting in-person; where we can catch-up and also make digital link verifications.  Talk to you soon I hope.  “</p>\n<p>Can the invite use the network in a probation mode so that SMS is not required and my phone number is not exposed?</p>\n<aside class=\"quote group-volunteer_moderators\" data-username=\"Herohtar\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"67672\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/herohtar/48/43780_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Herohtar:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Or how would you send them anything?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>If a contact(s) still have their Signal account active, could the invite transmit over the Signal network?</p>\n<p>Also, can the invite be personalized as in my example?</p>",
        "post_number": 4,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 5,
        "updated_at": "2025-03-14T17:30:00.562Z",
        "reply_count": 2,
